---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - BlissBox">
  <Navbar />
  
  <main class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="glass-card policy-card">
        <h1 class="gradient-text">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: May 9, 2026</p>
        
        <div class="policy-content">
          <section>
            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>At BlissBox, we believe that your music taste is your business. This Privacy Policy outlines how we handle your data in our privacy-focused streaming application. Unlike traditional platforms, we prioritize local processing and minimal data collection.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>As a YouTube Music / Streaming client focused on privacy, BlissBox collects minimal data:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Local Library Data:</strong> Information about your offline downloads and local playlists stays on your device.</li>
              <li><strong>Playback History:</strong> If enabled, history is stored locally to provide recommendations without being synced to a central server unless explicitly requested.</li>
              <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> If you choose to sync your account, only necessary authentication tokens are stored securely.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>3. How We Use Data</h2>
            <p>We use your data strictly to provide and improve the streaming experience:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>To switch between audio and video modes seamlessly.</li>
              <li>To manage your offline downloads and background playback.</li>
              <li>To provide a personalized UI based on your preferences.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>BlissBox interacts with external streaming APIs (like YouTube Music). While BlissBox itself does not track you, these third-party services may have their own privacy policies. We encourage you to review them.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>5. Security</h2>
            <p>We implement industry-standard encryption for any data that leaves your device and ensure that your privacy is never compromised for advertising purposes.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out via our GitHub or Telegram community.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    padding-top: 10rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .policy-card {
    padding: 4rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .policy-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-card {
      padding: 2rem;
    }
    
    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
